villages on storage,

00:09:03.520 --> 00:09:08.050 align:middle line:84%
or call it inventory, or
carryover, as well as the seed

00:09:08.050 --> 00:09:10.190 align:middle line:90%
that they put in the ground.

00:09:10.190 --> 00:09:12.440 align:middle line:84%
And I'll come back
to that momentarily.

00:09:12.440 --> 00:09:16.670 align:middle line:84%
And if you go back to the
economic science lecture,

00:09:16.670 --> 00:09:22.490 align:middle line:84%
this lecture is illustrative of
something we call calibration.

00:09:22.490 --> 00:09:26.290 align:middle line:84%
So you have a model of the
way the world works and you

00:09:26.290 --> 00:09:28.840 align:middle line:84%
find, somehow,
parameter values that

00:09:28.840 --> 00:09:30.850 align:middle line:90%
are appropriate for the model.

00:09:30.850 --> 00:09:34.270 align:middle line:84%
And then you simulate
the model and figure out

00:09:34.270 --> 00:09:36.290 align:middle line:90%
how well it fits the data.

00:09:36.290 --> 00:09:38.710 align:middle line:84%
And if it fits reasonably
well, then it's

00:09:38.710 --> 00:09:41.980 align:middle line:84%
a success, that you have
a logical explanation

00:09:41.980 --> 00:09:45.790 align:middle line:84%
of in an artificial economy
of how the world actually

00:09:45.790 --> 00:09:49.840 align:middle line:84%
works, or in this case,
past tense, was working.

00:09:49.840 --> 00:09:52.120 align:middle line:84%
There should be another
bullet point here.

00:09:52.120 --> 00:09:56.950 align:middle line:84%
Because I like to feature and
earmark that when it comes up,

00:09:56.950 --> 00:09:58.990 align:middle line:84%
we go through
various techniques.

00:09:58.990 --> 00:10:01.750 align:middle line:84%
And the technique that's
going to become apparent

00:10:01.750 --> 00:10:03.500 align:middle line:90%
is dynamic programming.

00:10:03.500 --> 00:10:07.420 align:middle line:84%
So most of the lectures up to
this point, not all of them

00:10:07.420 --> 00:10:09.340 align:middle line:90%
were static.

00:10:09.340 --> 00:10:12.430 align:middle line:84%
We made an exception with
that interest rate and income

00:10:12.430 --> 00:10:16.000 align:middle line:84%
and substitution effects and
a couple of the consumption

00:10:16.000 --> 00:10:17.230 align:middle line:90%
set diagrams.

00:10:17.230 --> 00:10:20.030 align:middle line:84%
So time is playing
a big role here.

00:10:20.030 --> 00:10:22.510 align:middle line:84%
And so if we're going to
solve a problem or program,

00:10:22.510 --> 00:10:24.640 align:middle line:84%
it's going to be
a dynamic program.

00:10:24.640 --> 00:10:26.590 align:middle line:84%
And there's some
useful techniques

00:10:26.590 --> 00:10:30.320 align:middle line:84%
that fall right out of
the end of this lecture.

00:10:30.320 --> 00:10:33.760 align:middle line:84%
So we're going to talk about
actual and potential use

00:10:33.760 --> 00:10:39.130 align:middle line:84%
of risk reduction arrangements,
namely carrying over grain

00:10:39.130 --> 00:10:40.970 align:middle line:90%
from one year to the next.

00:10:40.970 --> 00:10:43.660 align:middle line:84%
This first line
says alternative,

00:10:43.660 --> 00:10:46.690 align:middle line:84%
begging the issue of what
else have we looked at.

00:10:46.690 --> 00:10:50.500 align:middle line:84%
Well, we looked at an individual
putting his strips of land

00:10:50.500 --> 00:10:52.390 align:middle line:90%
all over the village.

00:10:52.390 --> 00:10:56.500 align:middle line:84%
And I referred to that as
portfolio diversification

00:10:56.500 --> 00:10:57.790 align:middle line:90%
at one point.

00:10:57.790 --> 00:11:00.530 align:middle line:84%
We looked at, and we
are about to see, again,

00:11:00.530 --> 00:11:03.830 align:middle line:84%
the picture of the estates
of the Bishop of Winchester,

00:11:03.830 --> 00:11:05.710 align:middle line:84%
which were spread
out over space,

00:11:05.710 --> 00:11:08.350 align:middle line:90%
arguably, again, to diversify.

00:11:08.350 --> 00:11:10.930 align:middle line:84%
And now we're going to
be stuck in one village,

00:11:10.930 --> 00:11:13.570 align:middle line:84%
and effectively, with one
person in one village,

00:11:13.570 --> 00:11:19.030 align:middle line:84%
on his or her own, looking for
alternative ways of reducing

00:11:19.030 --> 00:11:20.780 align:middle line:90%
exposure to risk.

00:11:20.780 --> 00:11:22.870 align:middle line:84%
Now the stylized
facts, if we go back

