00:52:33.650 --> 00:52:37.370 align:middle line:90%
with the rest of the economy.

00:52:37.370 --> 00:52:40.520 align:middle line:84%
And that's still referred to as
self-insurance, although it's

00:52:40.520 --> 00:52:43.910 align:middle line:90%
a bit misleading.

00:52:43.910 --> 00:52:48.440 align:middle line:84%
Because one person's saving
is another person's borrowing.

00:52:48.440 --> 00:52:51.120 align:middle line:84%
But anyway, we're not doing
the general equilibrium here.

00:52:51.120 --> 00:52:55.280 align:middle line:84%
We're taking-- the
interest rate is given.

00:52:55.280 --> 00:52:58.100 align:middle line:84%
But the other thing
would be, what

00:52:58.100 --> 00:53:02.110 align:middle line:84%
if there were multiple
people like this,

00:53:02.110 --> 00:53:06.880 align:middle line:84%
and some people had high
income at a given date,

00:53:06.880 --> 00:53:11.650 align:middle line:84%
and other people had low
income at a given date?

00:53:11.650 --> 00:53:14.590 align:middle line:84%
Then we're back
to thinking about

00:53:14.590 --> 00:53:16.945 align:middle line:84%
whether they could make
deals with each other.

00:53:16.945 --> 00:53:20.860 align:middle line:90%


00:53:20.860 --> 00:53:24.490 align:middle line:84%
So we'll get there
actually next time.

00:53:24.490 --> 00:53:28.770 align:middle line:84%
But the risk-sharing
problem would be--

00:53:28.770 --> 00:53:31.560 align:middle line:84%
an extreme version
of that is get rid

00:53:31.560 --> 00:53:34.020 align:middle line:84%
of the storage
altogether and the seed.

00:53:34.020 --> 00:53:34.698 align:middle line:90%
Get rid of them.

00:53:34.698 --> 00:53:36.240 align:middle line:84%
Not the seed, get
rid of the storage.

00:53:36.240 --> 00:53:38.130 align:middle line:90%
Get rid of the bond.

00:53:38.130 --> 00:53:41.130 align:middle line:84%
But imagine these guys can
contract with each other,

00:53:41.130 --> 00:53:45.030 align:middle line:84%
write financial contracts,
or informal risk-sharing

00:53:45.030 --> 00:53:47.970 align:middle line:84%
arrangements with
each other so as

00:53:47.970 --> 00:53:50.400 align:middle line:84%
to pool the risk
that they're facing.

00:53:50.400 --> 00:53:54.080 align:middle line:90%


00:53:54.080 --> 00:53:58.110 align:middle line:84%
Like in the village, they
had scattered those strips.

00:53:58.110 --> 00:54:02.450 align:middle line:84%
So they're trying to stabilize
their starting point.

00:54:02.450 --> 00:54:05.330 align:middle line:84%
But on top of it, they could
be borrowing and lending.

00:54:05.330 --> 00:54:08.780 align:middle line:90%
They could be making a deal.

00:54:08.780 --> 00:54:12.140 align:middle line:84%
